<DOC><DOCNO> AP890722-0066 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-22-89 1053EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Typhoon     07-22 0198</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Typhoon,0206</SECOND><HEAD>Rains Caused By Typhoon Hope Kill 24, Injure 1,000</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Torrential rains and floods caused by TyphoonHope have killed at least 24 people and injured 1,000 in easternChina, an official report said Saturday, just days after TyphoonGordon took at least 17 lives.   The Xinhua News Agency said up to 7{ inches of rain fell invarious counties of Fujian province during the 24 hours beginning 8a.m. Friday.   Torrents rushed down mountains and several rivers flooded,destroying 4,000 houses and covering 8,150 acres of cropland, thereport said.   It said one person was missing.   Typhoon Hope came ashore late Thursday in Zhejiang province,just north of Fujian, but no deaths were reported there.   Typhoon Gordon swept into southeastern China's Guangdongprovince on Tuesday. It killed 17 people and injured more than 100,while 13 were reported missing. Heavy damage also was done tocrops, bridges, highways and telecommunications.   Gordon first hit land Sunday in the Philippines, where it killed32 people. It killed on person in Hong Kong on Tuesday, officialssaid.   Flooding has killed a total of 1,400 people throughout Chinasince early June, according to official reports.</TEXT></DOC>